 Gwyneth Paltrow calls 'nepo baby' an “ugly moniker” as daughter starts modelling career https://www.nme.com/news/film/gwyneth-paltrow-calls-nepo-baby-ugly-moniker-daughter-starts-modelling-career-3518827?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=gwyneth-paltrow-calls-nepo-baby-ugly-moniker-daughter-starts-modelling-careerChris Edwards Fri, 20 Oct 2023 16:30:41 +0000 Film NewsNewsgw https://www.nme.com/?p=3518827 <p><img width="2144" height="1430" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow.jpg 2144w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-696x464.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-1392x928.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-1068x712.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2144px) 100vw, 2144px" /></p><p> &quot;There&#39;s nothing wrong with doing or wanting to do what your parents do&quot;</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/gwyneth-paltrow-calls-nepo-baby-ugly-moniker-daughter-starts-modelling-career-3518827">Gwyneth Paltrow calls &#39;nepo baby&#39; an “ugly moniker” as daughter starts modelling career</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2144" height="1430" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow.jpg 2144w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-800x534.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-696x464.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-1392x928.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Gwyneth-Paltrow-1068x712.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2144px) 100vw, 2144px" /></p><p> Gwyneth Paltrow has called the term &#39;nepo baby&#39; an “ugly moniker” and supported her daughter&#39;s career as a Chanel Model.</p><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.bustle.com/beauty/gwyneth-paltrow-good-clean-goop-interview" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Bustle</em></a> magazine, the Oscar-winning actress and businesswoman said that she hopes her children “feel free to pursue exactly what they want to do” without fear of judgement.</p><p> The term &#39;nepo baby&#39; refers to the children of celebrities who have success in similar careers. Nepo is short for nepotism.</p><p> The phrase went viral online last year as social media users drew attention to a number rising stars who have famous parents, such as Brooklyn Beckham, Jaden and Willow Smith, and <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/euphoria"><em>Euphoria</em></a> star Maude Apatow, who is the daughter of director Judd Apatow and actress Leslie Mann.</p><p> In January, Paltrow&#39;s 19-year-old daughter Apple Martin — whose father is <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/coldplay">Coldplay</a> singer <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/chris-martin">Chris Martin</a> — made her debut as a model at Chanel&#39;s Paris Fashion Week. </p><figure id="attachment_3518837" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3518837" style="width: 2084px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3518837" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin.jpg" alt="" width="2084" height="1242" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin.jpg 2084w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin-400x238.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin-800x477.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin-696x415.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin-1392x830.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Apple-Martin-1068x636.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2084px) 100vw, 2084px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3518837" class="wp-caption-text"> Apple Martin is the daughter of Gwyneth Paltrow and Chris Martin. Credit: Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Paltrow said that there is a “whole nepo baby culture and judgement that exists around kids of famous people”.</p><p> “She&#39;s really just a student, and… she just wants to be a kid and be at school and learn. But there&#39;s nothing wrong with doing or wanting to do what your parents do. Nobody rips on a kid who&#39;s like &#39;I want to be a doctor like my dad and granddad&#39;.</p><p> “The truth is, if you grow up in a house with a lot of artists and people making art and music, that&#39;s what you know, the same way that if you grow up in a house with law, the discussions around the table are about the nuances of whatever particular law the parents practice.</p><p> She added: “I think it&#39;s kind of an ugly moniker. I just hope that my children always feel free to pursue exactly what they want to do, irrespective of what anybody&#39;s going to think or say.”</p><p> Back in May, Paltrow reflected on her Oscars win in 1999 (Best Actress for <em>Shakespeare In Love</em> ), <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/gwyneth-paltrow-says-british-press-were-so-horrible-to-me-following-oscars-win-3439563">describing the reaction from the British press as being “so horrible”</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/gwyneth-paltrow-calls-nepo-baby-ugly-moniker-daughter-starts-modelling-career-3518827">Gwyneth Paltrow calls &#39;nepo baby&#39; an “ugly moniker” as daughter starts modelling career</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
